to the editor charles w kadlec how taxes trickle down op ed aug 1 supports the repeal of the estate tax and the lowering of income taxes because he thinks the poor not just the rich will benefit however the wealthiest 1 percent of americans doubled their share of our country 's wealth between 1976 and 1997 from 19 percent to 40 percent while the share of the bottom 90 percent plunged from 51 percent to 27 percent furthermore the estate tax is paid by only a tiny minority of people those lucky enough to be born in wealthy families why should n't they share their good fortune with the rest of society george levinger amherst mass aug 1 2000 the writer is professor emeritus of social psychology at the university of massachusetts

